Bring a large #pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; roughly chop leaves. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp for chicken.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

== Kale ==

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add kale and a splash of @water{}. Cook until kale is wilted and very tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: If necessary, cook kale in batches.

Stir in garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}; add lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Shrimp ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for kale over medium-high heat. Add @shrimp{10%ounce} in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Cook shrimp, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, 4-6 minutes.

== Creamy Parmesan Sauce ==

Transfer kale to pan with shrimp and reduce heat to medium low. Add @cream sauce base{4%ounce} and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Stir in 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce is combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add drained spaghetti and @butter{1%TBSP} to pan with sauce; toss to combine. Add a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.